Are States Leaking Voters’ Data?
The Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC) is under fire for illegally sharing sensitive voter data with at least one partisan nonprofit, according to lawsuits filed by the Thomas More Society against elections departments in Pennsylvania, Michigan, Wisconsin, and Minnesota.

While the lawsuits vary in their details, they all allege violations of the Help America Vote Act (HAVA), legislation from 2002 requiring states to maintain accurate statewide lists of registered and unregistered voters. HAVA does not authorize states to share this registration data with third-party organizations such as ERIC—effectively outsourcing its responsibilities to a private organization—since it is protected by federal law. #GlobalOligarchs #China #Owned
China Threatens To Fire Senators Who Voted For TikTok Ban
The Babylon Bee ^ | December 15, 2022 | The Babylon Bee
https://babylonbee.com/news/china-threatens-to-fire-senators-who-voted-for-tiktok-ban

BEIJING — China's President Xi issued a stern warning to American politicians this week, vowing that any members of Congress who dare to vote for a ban on TikTok will be fired from their jobs.

"We hired all you American legislators to do one job: weaken and destroy America from within," said Xi gravely. "If you can't prove your fealty to the glorious CCP who graciously put you in your position, it will go on your performance review, and trust me — you don't want that to happen."

Already, lawmakers in Washington are backing away from supporting legislation that would ban the use of TikTok on government devices, although they insist it has nothing to do with the Chinese threat. "I just really like TikTok!" said Representative Eric Swalwell. "Fang Fang is on there! Um, I mean, it's so fun and creative!"

"I believe we need to think twice about banning this wonderful app," said Senator Mitch McConnell. "Have you seen the dancing girls on there? Such talent!"

President Xi has warned any lawmakers running for reelection that he won't secretly support their campaigns unless they comply. At publishing time, Army Chief of Staff General Milley had instructed his entire chain of command to download the app.

Washington : le conseil rabbinique réuni par les juifs accuse Trump de tentative de coup d’état

La rédaction
Démocratie Participative
20 décembre 2022



Les États-Unis sont désormais une république bananière.

Le Parti démocrate (la CIA, c’est-à-dire les juifs) a réuni un conseil rabbinique pour accuser Donald Trump de complot contre l’Amérique (?!).

Il faut tout l’art juif de l’inversion accusatoire pour oser une telle manoeuvre contre Trump. Comme vous le savez, en 2020 ces juifs ont truqué les élections présidentielles avant de proclamer le vieillard sénile Biden « président ».

Il suffit de regarder les faciès des membres de ce sanhédrin pour comprendre ce qu’il se passe.

jean-eric branaa
@BranaaJean
·
Suivre
La commission recommande de poursuivre l'ancien président Donald Trump pour
▶️ Obstruction d'une procédure officielle
▶️ Complot pour frauder les Etats-Unis
▶️ Complot pour faire de fausses déclarations
▶️ "incitation", "assistance", "aide ou sympathie" en vue d'une insurrection

Un juif est apparu sur CNN parmi de très nombreux autres juifs pour assurer que Trump serait poursuivi pour coup d’état, Nick Akerman.

« Je pense que Donald Trump va être inculpé ».

L’ancien procureur spécial adjoint du Watergate, Nick Akerman, s’exprime sur ce qui pourrait arriver à Trump maintenant que les audiences du 6 janvier sont terminées.
CNN
@CNN
·
Suivre
"I think Donald Trump is going to be indicted."

Former Assistant Special Watergate Prosecutor Nick Akerman weighs in on what may happen to Trump now that the Jan. 6 hearings have concluded.
https://twitter.com/i/status/1605166754413568007

L’idée principale des juifs est d’empêcher Trump de se présenter aux primaires du Parti républicain.

Ils n’en veulent pas, ils ne veulent prendre aucun risque et désigner eux-mêmes l’opposant à Biden.

Ils vont donc le poursuivre pour coup d’état et, au vu des charges retenues par les putschistes juifs, Trump ne peut pas échapper à la prison.

Ce n’est pas une déclaration de guerre à Trump, mais une déclaration de guerre à tous les Américains, très majoritairement blancs, qui ont voté pour lui et voulaient continuer de voter pour lui.

En France, le régime est enthousiaste à cette idée.

franceinfo
@FranceInfo
·
Suivre
🔴 DIRECT 🗣 La Commission d’enquête sur l’attaque du Capitole recommande des poursuites pénales contre D. Trump ➡️ “Il faut comprendre que l’étau se resserre autour de Donald Trump”, estime Marie-Cécile Naves, directrice de recherche à l’IRIS.
https://twitter.com/i/status/1605077150679318528

Cette démocratie juive globale dans laquelle nous sommes réduits en esclavage joue sa survie, à l’extérieur comme à l’intérieur.

Ils veulent éradiquer toute résistance de nature nationale, identitaire au projet cosmopolite global de Davos.

La question est de savoir si Trump va faire autre chose que geindre sur son réseau social et appeler ses partisans à la révolution. S’il ne le fait pas, il sera arrêté, jugé par les juifs et incarcéré pour s’être opposé (mollement) aux élections truquées de 2020.

Ensuite, il sera assassiné dans sa cellule.

La balle est dans le camp du ministère de la Justice américain qui peut, ou non, poursuivre Trump.

Vous serez choqué d’apprendre que l’actuel ministre de la Justice américain est Merrick Garland, de son vrai nom Horwitz, un juif.

_source.content: A “cult” is deemed so because it claims to have faith in Jesus (wrong “Jesus”, but that’s another story), quote Scripture passages (WAY out of Biblical context) and fails to follow Him and Him ALONE. They do a good job of telling people about Jesus but fail to teach anyone about His finished work on the cross or His Resurrection. There’s ALWAYS someone else as a “leader”. Examples: Charles “Taze” Russell of Jehovah’s Witnesses, Moses of the Hebrew Roots Movement (an offshoot of the false religion of Judaism), the pope/a priest/Mary of Roman Catholicism, Mary Baker Eddy of Christian Science, Joseph Smith of Latter Day Saints, L. Ron Hubbard of Scientology, Ellen G. White of Seventh Day Adventism, Eric vonAnderseck of Second Eighth Week Apostles and so on. Additionally, there are no contradictions in Scripture...EVER. It’s cults which add to Calvary, not The Lord.An incorrect version of “Jesus” exists in ANY cult which includes those “salvation by works” people. It’s totally impossible to “earn a gift”. No “Jesus” in false religions. One doesn’t HAVE TO do things pertaining to Christianity, he or she GETS to. HUMONGOUS difference.) Christianity doesn’t teach anything like either “salvation by works” or “religion” (see Romans 6:23 for more information). Additionally, Scripture is BEYOND clear in 2 Corinthians 5:8 (absent with the body = present with The Lord). By contrast, salvation is “Just Jesus at Calvary and with His Resurrection. No artificial anything”. (“The Gospel ONLY”, in other words – Keyword: “ONLY”). Someone born again is only qualified to teach the new covenant (2 Corinthians 3:4-11). As such, that person is a partaker in the Divine Nature (2 Peter 1:3-4). We’re under grace. Jesus fulfilled 100% of the law. Because of that, He changes what you want should you decide to choose in His favor. (See Romans 5:10 and Hebrews 10:14 for more information.) People aren’t robots. Forever’s a long time.Will cheerfully do what The Lord says instead. Feel free to take matters up with The Author if there’s some “problem” with how He writes His Own Book. That 1-on-1 with The Lord happens with 100% of everyone whether he or she “believes that way or not” (see Hebrews 9:27-28). Confidence on the Day of Judgment is critical. Psalm 118:8 implies that it’s better to trust in The Lord than it is to put confidence in man.(SIDE NOTE - The term “Christ” is a title, not a name. It means either “The Anointed One” or “Messiah”.)Rather than ask, “What would Jesus do?” Perhaps instead inquire as to what He may be doing in you. It’s more accurate and allowing Him to live in you is more feasible than merely trying to imitate behavior(s).In Hebrews 10:14, “For all time” means (may I have a drumroll, please) “For all time”. (That’s spiritually-speaking, or course. The rest of you? Welcome to being human.)(ANOTHER SIDE NOTE – In some translations, “For all time” is worded as “Forever”, “To the end” or “For eternity”.)

They do a good job of telling people about Jesus but fail to teach anyone about His finished work on the cross or His Resurrection. There’s ALWAYS someone else as a “leader”. Examples: Charles “Taze” Russell of Jehovah’s Witnesses, Moses of the Hebrew Roots Movement (an offshoot of the false religion of Judaism), the pope/a priest/Mary of Roman Catholicism, Mary Baker Eddy of Christian Science, Joseph Smith of Latter Day Saints, L. Ron Hubbard of Scientology, Ellen G. White of Seventh Day Adventism, Eric vonAnderseck of Second Eighth Week Apostles and so on. Additionally, there are no contradictions in Scripture...EVER. It’s cults which add to Calvary, not The Lord.

An incorrect version of “Jesus” exists in ANY cult which includes those “salvation by works” people. It’s totally impossible to “earn a gift”. No “Jesus” in false religions. One doesn’t HAVE TO do things pertaining to Christianity, he or she GETS to. HUMONGOUS difference.) Christianity doesn’t teach anything like either “salvation by works” or “religion” (see Romans 6:23 for more information). Additionally, Scripture is BEYOND clear in 2 Corinthians 5:8 (absent with the body = present with The Lord).

By contrast, salvation is “Just Jesus at Calvary and with His Resurrection. No artificial anything”. (“The Gospel ONLY”, in other words – Keyword: “ONLY”). Someone born again is only qualified to teach the new covenant (2 Corinthians 3:4-11). As such, that person is a partaker in the Divine Nature (2 Peter 1:3-4). We’re under grace. Jesus fulfilled 100% of the law. Because of that, He changes what you want should you decide to choose in His favor. (See Romans 5:10 and Hebrews 10:14 for more information.) People aren’t robots. Forever’s a long time.

Will cheerfully do what The Lord says instead. Feel free to take matters up with The Author if there’s some “problem” with how He writes His Own Book. That 1-on-1 with The Lord happens with 100% of everyone whether he or she “believes that way or not” (see Hebrews 9:27-28). Confidence on the Day of Judgment is critical. Psalm 118:8 implies that it’s better to trust in The Lord than it is to put confidence in man.

(SIDE NOTE - The term “Christ” is a title, not a name. It means either “The Anointed One” or “Messiah”.)

Rather than ask, “What would Jesus do?” Perhaps instead inquire as to what He may be doing in you. It’s more accurate and allowing Him to live in you is more feasible than merely trying to imitate behavior(s).

In Hebrews 10:14, “For all time” means (may I have a drumroll, please) “For all time”. (That’s spiritually-speaking, or course. The rest of you? Welcome to being human.)
(ANOTHER SIDE NOTE – In some translations, “For all time” is worded as “Forever”, “To the end” or “For eternity”.)

BTW, this site is not dedicated to COVID & Vaccinations. You are invited to post that stuff at https://gab.com/groups/1892
